      },
      {
        title: 'Yrsel',
        description:
          'Bedömning av cervikogen yrsel och balansbesvär. Trygg guidning och anpassad rehabilitering.',
        icon: 'flat-color-icons:business-contact',
      },
      {
        title: 'Käk/huvudvärk',
        description: 'Spänningar i käke och tinningar som ger huvudvärk. Behandling och egenvårdsråd för bestående resultat.',
        icon: 'flat-color-icons:database',
      },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Features2>

  <!-- HighlightedPosts Widget ******* -->

  <BlogLatestPosts
    title="Tips and advice from the clinic"
    information={`In the blog, I share practical advice, exercises and insights about common problems in back, neck, shoulders, knees and feet.
                        My goal is to help you understand the causes of the pain and what you can do yourself between treatments.`}
  >
  <Fragment slot="bg">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
  </Fragment></BlogLatestPosts>

  <!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

  <FAQs
    title="Frequently asked questions"
    subtitle="Here I answer the most common questions from my patients in Enköping. If you have other questions, feel free to contact me directly."
    classes={{ container: 'max-w-6xl' }}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'How long does a treatment take?',
        description:
          'A first consultation usually takes 45-60 minutes where we do a thorough examination and discuss your problems. Subsequent treatments take 30-45 minutes. We take the time needed for you to get the best possible care.',
      },
      {
        title: 'How much does a treatment cost?',
        description:
          'We follow the county tax of 200 kronor per treatment. Free card applies of course. We also offer package solutions for those who need several treatments. Contact me for more information about prices.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Do I need a referral from a doctor?',
        description:
          'No, you can contact me directly for most problems within naprapathy and physiotherapy. If needed, I can refer you to a doctor or other specialist care.',
      },
      {
        title: 'How many treatments are usually needed?',
        description:
          'It varies a lot depending on the type of problem and how long you have had them. Acute problems can often be relieved in 1-3 treatments, while chronic conditions may need 5-10 treatments or more. I always make an individual assessment.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Can I continue training during treatment?',
        description:
          'In most cases, you can continue training, but I always advise on which exercises are suitable and which should be avoided temporarily. The goal is for you to be able to return to your normal activity level as soon as possible.',
      },
      {
        title: 'What is the difference between naprapath and physiotherapist?',
        description:
          'As both a naprapath and licensed physiotherapist, I combine the best of both worlds. Naprapathy focuses on manual treatment of joints and muscles, while physiotherapy includes rehabilitation and preventive training.',
      },
    ]}
  />
